protests that erupted
in West Baltimore after
25-year-old Freddie

40:40.338 --> 40:45.376 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Gray died while in police
custody brought
attention to the staggering
poverty and violence

40:45.476 --> 40:48.379 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the city's impoverished
neighborhoods.

40:48.479 --> 40:53.051 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Sandtown-Winchester, where
Gray lived,
the dismal health and low life
expectancy

40:53.151 --> 40:58.289 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rivals some of the world's
poorest countries.
That's especially striking in a
city world-renowned

40:58.389 --> 41:01.225 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for its prestigious medical
schools and public
health research.

41:01.326 --> 41:07.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Men and women in Sandtown live,
on average,
just 69 years, a decade below
the rest of

41:07.398 --> 41:18.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the country. Health officials
say infants
here die at almost twice the
national average.

41:18.743 --> 41:24.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And adults are felled by heart
disease, prostate
cancer and AIDS with shocking
frequency.

41:24.415 --> 41:29.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Pastor Derrick DeWitt of First
Mount Calvary
Baptist Church in Sandtown prays
for an end

41:29.821 --> 41:32.657 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to his neighborhood's ill
health, but preaches
self-reliance.

41:32.757 --> 41:35.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. DERRICK DEWITT, First Mount
Calvary Baptist
Church: You have to make sure
that you are

41:35.126 --> 41:40.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
getting the health care that you
need. Things
are not equal, and they probably
will never

41:40.531 --> 41:42.400 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
be equal.

41:42.500 --> 41:46.537 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Pastor DeWitt,
like many residents
here, is deeply distrustful of
Baltimore's

41:46.637 --> 41:51.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hospitals. He learned to be wary
of nearby
Bon Secours Hospital early on
from his grandmother,

41:51.743 --> 41:54.078 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who was a member of the church
he now leads.

41:54.178 --> 41:59.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. DERRICK DEWITT: All of our
family who
went to Bon Secours never came
out of Bon

41:59.250 --> 42:06.290 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Secours. So, she kind of
instilled in us,
"Never take me there. If I ever
have to go

42:06.391 --> 42:10.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the hospital, never take me
there." And
that attitude still exists
today.

42:10.695 --> 42:15.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SARAH VARNEY: But in an
emergency, Bon Secours
is one of the closest hospitals
to Sandtown-Winchester.

42:15.233 --> 42:20.138 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
REV. DERRICK DEWITT: My
directive is, if you
have to put me in the car, take
me to a hospital

42:20.238 --> 42:24.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
other than Bon Secours, because
the nickname
for Bon Secours, do you know
what that is?

42:25.042 --> 42:25.877 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SARAH VARNEY: Tell me.

42:25.977 --> 42:27.745 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
REV. DERRICK DEWITT: "Bon
se-killer."

42:27.845 --> 42:31.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Bon Secours is
working mightily
to change that reputation, but
the distrust

42:31.549 --> 42:37.388 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
goes beyond just one hospital.
Stories dating
back to the 1800s that so-called
night doctors

42:37.488 --> 42:42.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
kidnapped black children for
medical experiments
are vividly remembered.

42:43.027 --> 42:48.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Experimentation was, in fact,
happening to
black Americans nationwide. At
Johns Hopkins,

42:48.199 --> 42:52.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
researchers famously took tissue
cells from
Henrietta Lacks, a black cancer
patient, without

42:53.070 --> 42:54.906 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
permission in 1951.

42:55.006 --> 42:58.443 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
EDDIE REAVES, Baltimore
Resident: To me, they
have always been like that.
Never did like

42:58.543 --> 43:00.411 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Johns Hopkins.

43:00.511 --> 43:04.081 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Eddie Reaves, age
64, is a member
of Pastor DeWitt's church. His
partner died

43:04.182 --> 43:08.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
two years ago after doctors at
Johns Hopkins
operated on her heart.

43:08.252 --> 43:12.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EDDIE REAVES: From day one,
before she even
went in, I never liked them,
because that's

43:12.557 --> 43:15.159 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
all they do is experiment, to
me, on people.

43:15.259 --> 43:19.330 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Reaves is equally
skeptical
of other Baltimore hospitals. He
spent much

43:19.430 --> 43:24.368 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of his life addicted to drugs,
and when his
diabetes and asthma spiraled out
of control,

43:24.469 --> 43:26.170 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
he would end up in the E.R.

43:26.270 --> 43:30.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But even after he got off drugs
and signed
up for health insurance, Reaves
found the

43:30.708 --> 43:34.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
medical system was a maze of
doctors who charged
too much and didn't listen to
him.

43:35.046 --> 43:38.816 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EDDIE REAVES: When the doctor
give me something
that give me side effect, I
don't take my

43:38.916 --> 43:43.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
medication. He said, why are you
not taking
it? I said, because it give me
side effects.

43:43.821 --> 43:49.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, sometimes, they think it's
a big joke,
but I don't take nothing that
give me side

43:49.660 --> 43:51.429 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
effects.

43:51.529 --> 43:54.031 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Dr. Samuel Ross,
the CEO of
Bon Secours, is well aware of
his hospital's

43:54.131 --> 43:57.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
reputation in the neighborhood,
and what it's
going to take to earn people's
trust.

43:58.069 --> 44:00.905 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DR. SAMUEL ROSS, CEO, Bon
Secours Hospital:
You often find out that a lot is
urban myth.

44:01.005 --> 44:06.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we also have to sit down and
say, well,
tell me why you feel that way?
And then, let

44:06.711 --> 44:09.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
me show you some things that may
cause you
to feel a different way.

44:09.847 --> 44:14.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Nearby, at the
University of
Maryland, Baltimore, president
Dr. Jay Perman

44:14.619 --> 44:18.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
says repairing the relationship
with black
Baltimoreans will take a long
time.

44:18.489 --> 44:20.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. JAY PERMAN, President,
University of Maryland,
Baltimore: I think there's still
too much

44:20.725 --> 44:31.202 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of a perception that we
experiment. Now, that
is not the case. Care is
rigorously delivered

44:31.302 --> 44:38.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with consent from the patient
always. But
it takes a long time, I think,
for people

44:38.309 --> 44:43.314 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to understand that the days of
hidden experimentation
are over.

44:43.414 --> 44:49.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Making that case
is not only
a moral imperative, but now a
financial one.

44:49.420 --> 44:52.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
While Freddie Gray's death and
the street
protests have called attention
to the health

44:52.657 --> 44:56.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
problems in Baltimore's poorest
neighborhoods,
sweeping changes to the health
care system

44:56.827 --> 45:01.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have forced hospitals to go
after their root
cause. Because of the Affordable
Care Act

45:01.132 --> 45:04.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and a change to the way Maryland
pays for
medical care, health
professionals are being

45:05.002 --> 45:09.607 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pushed to look more closely at
the details
of their patients' lives.

45:09.707 --> 45:13.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Public health researchers say
it's when patients
are in their neighborhoods, in
crowded homes

45:13.411 --> 45:18.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or decaying public schools, with
no grocery
stores or reliable buses that
health problems

45:18.583 --> 45:20.384 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
fester.

45:20.484 --> 45:24.255 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. JAY PERMAN: In the past, we
have always
thought about making correct
diagnoses, and

45:24.355 --> 45:30.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
preparing the right prescription
or therapeutic
plan, and then sending the
patient out.

45:30.127 --> 45:36.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think it's the fact that
we didn't focus
-- we in general in the American
health care

45:36.767 --> 45:43.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
system didn't focus on what
happens to the
patient when they're not
directly in our care

45:43.674 --> 45:45.376 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and in front of us.

45:45.476 --> 45:50.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: So, hospitals are
aiming to
fix the everyday problems that
are making

45:51.048 --> 45:56.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their patients sick. And there's
renewed urgency.
Hospitals can now face financial
consequences

45:56.687 --> 46:01.058 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from the federal government and
the state
of Maryland for failing to
prevent their patients

46:01.158 --> 46:04.729 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from returning to the E.R. for
avoidable problems.

46:04.829 --> 46:10.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Maryland legislature has
pressed for changes
too. A 2012 law established five
health enterprise

46:11.035 --> 46:19.110 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
zones which offer tax credits
and grants to
bring health care resources to
poor communities.

46:19.210 --> 46:23.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Driving that effort are groups
like the Coordinating
Center, which are paid by the
health enterprise

46:23.648 --> 46:28.653 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
zones to visit high-risk
patients, like Toni
Settles, just after they leave
Bon Secours,

46:28.753 --> 46:33.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the University of Maryland and
other Baltimore
hospitals. Advocates go into
patients' homes

46:33.424 --> 46:35.793 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to figure out how to keep their
recovery on
track.

46:35.893 --> 46:40.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENN SULIN-STAIR, Coordinating
Center: Will
you need help with planning
finances to afford

46:40.297 --> 46:42.099 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
those things?

46:42.199 --> 46:46.270 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Jenn Sulin-Stair
is part coach,
part confidant, part fixer who
first had to

46:46.370 --> 46:48.172 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
earn Settles' trust.

46:48.272 --> 46:50.374 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TONI SETTLES, Baltimore
Resident: It wasn't
a whole lot of talk. She put
action to it,

46:50.474 --> 46:54.912 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
you know, and set up
appointments for me and
then set up dates. And that's
the difference.

46:55.012 --> 46:59.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I never had nobody one on one,
no indeed.
They will say one thing, do
another.

46:59.617 --> 47:05.089 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SARAH VARNEY: The health
enterprise zones
pay for this kind of help for
two months.

47:05.189 --> 47:09.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Senior vice president Carol
Marsiglia says,
without an intervention, half of
high-risk

47:09.760 --> 47:14.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
patients return to the hospital
within 12
days. Although mental illness
and substance

47:14.899 --> 47:19.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
abuse can play a big role,
Marsiglia says
the grinding realities of
poverty often derail

47:19.904 --> 47:24.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
recovery, a broken wheelchair or
no money
to fill a prescription or get a
needed oxygen

47:24.775 --> 47:26.677 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
tank.

47:26.777 --> 47:29.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAROL MARSIGLIA, Coordinating
Center: So,
we do work to try to find some
financial resources,

47:29.213 --> 47:33.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
get that co-pay paid, so that
the person can
get the oxygen they need.
Otherwise, they

47:34.051 --> 47:36.987 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
may likely be back in the
hospital early the
next week.

47:37.088 --> 47:42.827 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: But for many, the
obstacles
just keep on coming. David Kelly
Jr., an outreach

47:42.927 --> 47:47.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
worker from LIGHT Health and
Wellness, a West
Baltimore community center, has
been counseling

47:47.465 --> 47:52.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Anthony Chase for years. The two
drive to
a mall parking lot to have a
private and frank

47:53.037 --> 47:57.608 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
conversation about keeping
Chase's HIV and
bipolar disorder under control.

47:57.708 --> 48:00.377 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: I'm working on myself right
now. I'm
working on all of me.

48:00.478 --> 48:02.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID KELLY JR., LIGHT Health
and Wellness:
Well, a big part of that is
going to be definitely

48:02.847 --> 48:07.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
maintaining your treatment
adherence, I think.
If you use that as a foundation
and build

48:07.785 --> 48:10.321 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from that, you know, everything
else sort
of...

48:10.421 --> 48:12.256 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: Yes, falls in place.

48:12.356 --> 48:17.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: The hospitals,
too, have renewed
their focus on West Baltimore. A
well-respected

48:17.294 --> 48:23.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
homeless clinic recently opened
up inside
Bon Secours, and the hospital is
converting

48:23.134 --> 48:28.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a church near Sandtown into a
clinic that
will offer primary care, mental
health counseling

48:28.372 --> 48:29.907 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and social services.

48:30.007 --> 48:33.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: First step, pour the milk
into a bag,
and then you measure the
vanilla.

48:33.711 --> 48:37.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: And the University
of Maryland,
Baltimore, is partnering with
public schools

48:37.481 --> 48:42.686 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
to inspire young
African-Americans to become
health care professionals, and
training current

48:42.787 --> 48:47.224 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
medical students to delve more
deeply into
the social conditions that
perpetuate poor

48:47.324 --> 48:49.260 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
health.

48:49.360 --> 48:54.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At Pastor DeWitt's church, Johns
Hopkins recently
held focus groups to ask
residents why they

48:54.365 --> 48:59.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
used the emergency room instead
of going to
a doctor's office. But it's not
clear if these

48:59.403 --> 49:04.408 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
intensive efforts will be
sustained. Funding
for the health enterprise zones
expires next

49:04.508 --> 49:06.210 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
year.

49:06.310 --> 49:09.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And many here are asking how far
hospitals
can go, even when threatened
with financial

49:09.880 --> 49:13.017 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
penalties to fix toxic
neighborhoods.

49:13.117 --> 49:17.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For his part, Reaves remains
unconvinced that
all the attention the protests
brought to

49:17.354 --> 49:20.291 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his neighborhood over this last
year will
do much good.

49:20.391 --> 49:24.728 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EDDIE REAVES: Things will get
worser and worser
to me, but you got to keep on
living, though,

49:24.829 --> 49:25.863 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
do what you got to do.

49:25.963 --> 49:27.698 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: It's a fatalism
hard-earned.

49:27.798 --> 49:33.938 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour" and
Kaiser Health News,
I'm Sarah Varney in Baltimore.

49:34.038 --> 49:39.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And a postscript
to our report:
Johns Hopkins officials say they
are committed

49:39.543 --> 49:43.347 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
