and what it conveyed about the
man.

50:38.936 --> 50:40.738 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Here's an excerpt.

50:40.838 --> 50:45.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EDWARD GERO, "The Originalist":
The court
has been my theater, and I have
the costumes.

50:45.476 --> 50:50.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: In the new play
"The Originalist,"
the first thing you notice about
actor Edward

50:50.514 --> 50:55.686 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Gero is his striking physical
resemblance
to the character he's playing,
the real-life

50:55.786 --> 50:57.955 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Supreme Court Justice Antonin
Scalia.

50:58.055 --> 51:07.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EDWARD GERO: I tell people what
they don't
want to hear. That's also what
makes me a

51:07.498 --> 51:12.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
monster. That's how half the
country see me,
aggressive, combative, law and
order conservative.

51:12.970 --> 51:21.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Other half sees me as a hero,
aggressive,
